  <main>
    <section class="hero home-hero home-hero-v2">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy reveal">
          <p class="hero-name">Zhansaya Kyrgyzmolda</p>
          <h1><span>Junior AI Researcher</span><span><span class="amp">&amp;</span> Engineer</span></h1>
          <p class="lede">I study Artificial Intelligence at Pusan National University. I work on NLP, computer vision, robotics, embedded systems, and AI applications.</p>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="#work">View projects</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="resume.html">View resume</a>
          </div>

          <div class="availability">
            <span></span>
            Busan, South Korea · Open to internships and junior roles
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-robot reveal delay" aria-label="Digital human connection illustration">
          <div class="hero-visual-panel">
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Abstract digital illustration of two connected hands made of blue lines">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a class="scroll-cue" href="#identity">VIEW MORE <span>↓</span></a>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="identity">
      <div class="section-label reveal"><span>01</span><p>ABOUT</p></div>

      <div class="split-intro">
        <h2 class="reveal">I am an AI student focused on NLP, computer vision, robotics, and human–computer interaction.</h2>
        <div class="reveal delay">
          <p>I use Python and related tools to build prototypes, test research questions, and document results. My work includes a language-model memory benchmark, a Raspberry Pi sign-language translator, an Arduino gesture glove, and an AI productivity web app.</p>
          <p>I am currently studying Artificial Intelligence at Pusan National University in Busan. I am looking for junior, internship, research assistant, and remote roles where I can continue developing practical AI systems.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="domain-grid">
        <article class="domain-card reveal">
          <span>01 / LANGUAGE</span>
          <h3>Natural Language Processing</h3>
          <p>LLM applications, retrieval, external memory, semantic evaluation, prompt behavior, and conversational system design.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="domain-card reveal delay">
          <span>02 / PERCEPTION</span>
          <h3>Computer Vision</h3>
          <p>Real-time hand tracking, gesture classification, OpenCV pipelines, MediaPipe landmarks, and camera-based interfaces.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="domain-card reveal">
          <span>03 / EMBODIMENT</span>
          <h3>Robotics &amp; Embedded AI</h3>
          <p>Raspberry Pi, Arduino, sensors, Bluetooth, local inference, and integration between model output and physical devices.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="domain-card reveal delay">
          <span>04 / INTERACTION</span>
          <h3>Human–Computer Interaction</h3>
          <p>Accessibility research, wearable input, user interviews, and interface design.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="work">
      <div class="section-label reveal"><span>02</span><p>SELECTED PROJECTS</p></div>

      <div class="section-title-row">
        <h2 class="reveal">Projects based on research, implementation, testing, and documentation.</h2>
        <p class="reveal delay">I explain what I built, how I tested it, what worked, what did not work, and what I plan to improve.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="work-grid">
        <a class="work-card ray-card reveal" href="ray.html">
          <div class="work-visual">
            <img src="assets/images/ui/ray-system.svg" alt="Project RAY memory system concept diagram">
          </div>
          <div class="work-copy">
            <div class="eyeline"><span>RESEARCH / NLP / ROBOTICS</span><span>2026 · ACTIVE</span></div>
            <h3>Project RAY</h3>
            <p>I am testing how external memory influences a frozen language model, with the long-term goal of using memory in a humanoid agent.</p>
            <div class="card-arrow">View project <span>↗</span></div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="work-card reveal delay" href="sign-language.html">
          <div class="work-visual">
            <img src="assets/images/projects/sign-demo-c.jpg" alt="Sign language recognition demonstration">
          </div>
          <div class="work-copy">
            <div class="eyeline"><span>COMPUTER VISION / ACCESSIBILITY</span><span>2022 · AWARD WINNER</span></div>
            <h3>Sign Language Translator</h3>
            <p>I built a Raspberry Pi prototype that recognizes fingerspelled letters using MediaPipe landmarks and geometric rules.</p>
            <div class="card-arrow">View project <span>↗</span></div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="work-card reveal" href="glove.html">
          <div class="work-visual">
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Gesture-controlled smart glove prototype close-up">
          </div>
          <div class="work-copy">
            <div class="eyeline"><span>EMBEDDED HCI / WEARABLES</span><span>2026 · PROTOTYPE</span></div>
            <h3>Gesture-Controlled Smart Glove</h3>
            <p>I built an Arduino-based wearable prototype for cursor control and air-drawing experiments using hand motion and sensor input.</p>
            <div class="card-arrow">View project <span>↗</span></div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a class="work-card reveal delay" href="doit.html">
          <div class="work-visual">
            <img src="assets/images/projects/doit-home.png" alt="DOIT AI productivity app homepage">
          </div>
          <div class="work-copy">
            <div class="eyeline"><span>LLM PRODUCT / WEB APP</span><span>PROTOTYPE</span></div>
            <h3>DOIT</h3>
            <p>I developed a web-app prototype that combines an AI chatbot, task generation, a calendar, notifications, daily check-ins, and focus tools.</p>
            <div class="card-arrow">View project <span>↗</span></div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section metrics-section">
      <div class="metric"><strong data-count="14">0</strong><span>cases where external memory dominated</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong data-count="27">0</strong><span>of 30 cases with positive memory gain</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong data-count="5">0</strong><span>research interviews for accessibility design</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong data-count="1">0</strong><span>national first-place robotics project award</span></div>
